subSubSection.paragraph:
Pereopod-2
(
Fig. 7C
) coxa with one seta; basis naked, four times longer than wide; ischium with two ventral setae; merus 0.3 times as long as basis, two times longer than wide; carpus long and distally wider, 1.4 times longer than merus, 2.4 times longer than wide, distal margin with one dorsal seta, one ventral spine and one ventral bayonet spine, which nearly 0.7 times as long as carpus; propodus long and slender, 1.1 times longer than carpus, over four times longer than wide, dorsal margin with one small distal spinule, ventral margin with one distal spine; dactylus plus unguis (
Fig. 7D
) approximately sigmoid, unguis longer than dactylus, duckbill-like.
